===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|capital}}, borrowed from {{der|en|la|capitālis|t=of the head}} (in sense “head of [[cattle]]”), from {{m|la|caput|t=head}} ({{cog|en|cap}}). Use in trade and finance originated in Medieval economies when a common but expensive transaction involved trading heads of cattle.

Compare {{doublet|en|chattel|kith and kine|t2=all one’s possessions|notext=1}}, which also use “cow” to mean “property”.

